Hello I Visited  your store #534 on 2/10/20. I ordered a dulce de leche milk shake and requested that the milk shake be made to a thick consistency.  The person who made my milk shake was not pleasant at all , he acted annoyed as if he didnt want to service me (my receipt says the persons name is Habib R). I had to ask for caramel  even though my milk shake comes with it. When I received my milk shake it was as if it was milk poured in a cup with caramel . It was extremely liquidy/thin and not the thick consistency I requested.  When I expressed that I was unhappy and that, that was not what I requested.  The  unpleasant sales person replied "oh well I gave u extra icecream". I explained that I didnt ask for extra icecream  I asked for a thick milk shake which means adding less milk, then I requested that he make me another. Said person replied that I would have to pay for another shake if I wanted another shake made.  After already spending $8.95 on a small shake I refused to pay again.  Of all the years I've visited your many stores I've never been so disappointed,  disgusted and never have I ever felt buyers remorse after purchasing ice cream, until now. I will never visit this location again. Not only was I out of money , I didnt have a shake that I drove 20min for.

I like to consider myself an ice cream milkshake connoisseur, always trying shakes from different places. I ordered a mint chip shake here, and was very disappointed. Although Haagen Dazs is known for their premium ice cream, the shake was subpar-very diluted. When I asked the employee, why it’s so diluted, he replied “I follow the ingredients, if you want thicker, I add more ice cream, but you pay $3 more” and refused to correct it.  First of all, a milkshake is supposed to be thick, not all watery. Secondly, if I’m paying $6.xx for a shake, I expect a quality shake from a reputable company. Asking me to pay $3 more to make it right, is unacceptable. Thirdly, please train your employees on how to do their job correctly. Customer service makes a huge difference, and it was unexpected here.  Save yourself the disappointment, and get a thick Mcflurry for a fraction of the price.
